******
[2] Netherlands: Surveillance in 10km zone around outbreak
Date: Mon 24 Nov 2014
Source: RTVOOST (Regional TV East, Netherlands) [in Dutch, trans. Mod.AS, summarised, edited]
http://www.rtvoost.nl/nieuws/default.aspx?nid=204281


32 chicken farms in the 10km zone around the infected farms in Kamperveen have been tested [by PCR]; no virus has been detected. Yet, the owners remain cautious. A poultry farm holder from the Mastenbroek Polder said: "We are really relieved, but we remain cautious."

Due to the quarantine measures applied, 200 000 eggs were withheld on the farm; so far, the damage has not been serious since they will be picked up today [24 Nov 2014]. However, the precautions should be kept in force for the time being [see item 3].

In the adjacent village, Kamperveen, the [HPAI H5N8] virus was discovered on 2 farms; eventually, all birds were culled on 3 farms.

