[On 20 Nov 2014, EU's Standing Committee on Plants, Animals, Food and Feed (Section Animal Health & Welfare) held an extraordinary meeting in Brussels to exchange views and opinions on a draft of "Commission Implementing Decision concerning certain protective measures in relation to HPAI H5N8 in the Netherlands and the UK." During the meeting, the Netherlands, Germany and UK delivered their respective presentations on HPAI H5N8.

The report of the EU reference laboratory for avian influenza at Weybridge [UK] was presented by the lab's director, Ian Brown. Its summary is copied above. Subscribers are encouraged to approach the full report, which includes results of surveillance activities of wild birds in member states and extensive additional information on the current H5N8 HPAI virus strain worldwide: its origin, tests, genotyping results, and more. The reports of the 3 affected European countries include useful information (see at http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/presentations_en.htm).

According to the Dutch follow-up report No. 2 to the OIE dated 22 Nov 2014, the outbreak in Kamperveen (in the eastern province Overijssel), confirmed as caused by HPAI H5N8, has thus become the 3rd Dutch outbreak since 14 Nov 2014. The affected population is "breeding poultry." Out of 10 000 susceptible birds on the farm, there were 500 recorded clinical cases (all died); 9500 remaining animals were destroyed.

The report, including an interactive map, is available at
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16566. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2986950,21437.]
